[normal]It is interesting
[normal] to note that on the subject of
[normal] the 
[normal]Savile
[normal] scandal, in June 2002 the BBC broadcast, ‘Hunt for 
[normal]Britain
[normal]’s Paedophiles’ on BBC Two.   This programme generated large n
[normal]umbers of complaints for its graphic content.  The video footage, photos, ‘sex’ drawings, taped telephone conversations
[normal] of paedophiles with children, and verbal descriptions (including bad language) were so explicit they might have helped to: develop an in
[normal]terest in paedophilia in some vulnerable adults and desensitise others;  give existing paedophiles guidance on how to target and groom children; traumatise some child viewers, or lead them to develop a precocious sexual interest and lastly create the sort 
[normal]of hysteria which can lead to dangerous vigilantism. 
