[normal]1.  
[normal]T
[normal]he number of television
[normal] channels
[normal]. The BBC should have fewer television channels and would do well to focus on the audience as a whole,
[normal] and treat everyone with equal respect and provide equal quality.   The current situation regarding television breaks the population down into groupings: the populist BBC One; the more serious BBC Two and BBC Four (BBC Four was be
[normal]st rated channel in 2011)
[normal],
[normal]  and
[normal] 
[normal]BBC Three for younger audiences (we are not going to discuss children’s programming here).
[normal]    By targeting different groups this ghettoises viewing and does little to raise aspiration or promote family viewing and link g
[normal]enerations.   
